# Master design gate

Full document: **`docs/goblin-warrens-design.md`**

## When this applies

Every design, feature, refactor, or scope decision. Read the relevant section before coding.

## North star

Above-ground goblin colony survival builder. Grow a filthy camp into a monster warren. Light RTS controls for clarity; **warren management is primary**.

## Never without explicit user reversal

- Underground / tunnel / cave-layer / digging mechanics
- Converting the game back to pure RTS
- Removing colony-survival systems to simplify combat
- Rewriting or breaking the gather-return-store worker loop
- Skipping milestone order (§37) to build advanced systems early

## Thematic names ≠ underground

Warren, Pit, Den, Burial Grounds, pit traps = **above-ground** visuals and buildings.

## MVP target

Survive 7 days and repel the first human raid. Prove goblin management is fun, dangerous, and memorable.

## Implementation order (summary)

1. Worker loop (preserve existing)
2. Selection + right-click commands
3. Building placement + construction
4. Food + population
5. Breeder Hut + Foblins
6. Combat → raids → magic → burial → 7-day demo loop

## Acceptance criteria (every feature)

Files changed · added · preserved · how to test · limitations · next step.
